annotations.description: The Carajillo hails from Spain and it is a coffee drink typically served with breakfast in working class neighborhoods: A shot of espresso over ice alongside...
annotations.title: Master The Classics: Carajillo

textContent:
1.5oz (45ml) Licor 43
.5oz (15ml) Mezcal (or Brandy)
Double Shot Espresso

Stir liquors over ice in glass. 
Pour espresso over.
